data.name: ping.ToolTip
data.value:
Tick this box to send an email message every number of minutes to the right.
This will ocnfirm that TeboCam is still functioning.
The email will contain: -Log file -Graph of movement for the day -A picture taken from the webcam(s) just before the email is sent
If the "All Cameras" radio button is selected, an image consisting of a mosaic of images from all cameras will be sent in the email. Otherwise the camera used for the ping is the camera mapped to the selected(green) button on the webcam tab.

data.name: pulseFreq.ToolTip
data.value:
The frequency of pulses in values up to 1.
The frequency relates to pulses per minute so 0.5 will pulse every 2 minutes and 0.25 will pulse every 4 minutes.
The recommended value is 0.5

data.name: button15.ToolTip
data.value:
Test that FreezeGuard is operating correctly.
This will turn off the pulse on TeboCam. FreezeGuard will then detect that TeboCam has frozen, TeboCam will then be restarted.
It may take up to 2 minutes before TeboCam is restarted after this button is clicked on - if you change your mind after clicking this button you can click on it again to restart the pulse.

data.name: freezeGuardOff.ToolTip
data.value:
FreezeGuard protects your TeboCam session from freezing. Better put if your TeboCam session freezes FreezeGuard will restart TeboCam with motion detection at the setting it was at just before TeboCam froze.
This enables you to have peace of mind when you are away from home for some time, as you can be assured that if TeboCam does freeze (and although it shouldn't even the best of programs occasionally freezes) Tebocam will restart without your intervention.
Freezeguard works by listening to the pulse of TeboCam and restarting TeboCam if it does not hear the pulse for a specified time period.

data.name: freezeGuardOn.ToolTip
data.value:
FreezeGuard protects your TeboCam session from freezing. Better put if your TeboCam session freezes FreezeGuard will restart TeboCam with motion detection at the setting it was at just before TeboCam froze.
This enables you to have peace of mind when you are away from home for some time, as you can be assured that if TeboCam does freeze (and although it shouldn't even the best of programs occasionally freezes) Tebocam will restart without your intervention.
Freezeguard works by listening to the pulse of TeboCam and restarting TeboCam if it does not hear the pulse for a specified time period.

data.name: button19.ToolTip
data.value:
Sometimes things go wrong!
The config file holds all your webcam(s) information, as well as other information relating to TeboCam. It also holds your encrypted password and email information.
Under certain circumstances it is possible to corrupt the config file. By vaulting the config file you are storing a copy of config file in a place where it cannot be corrupted by TeboCam. The vault folder is a read only folder for TeboCam.
You can recover the vaulted version at any point by clicking on the "Restore Profiles" button.
